g.text: A new purchase requisition is created with every export.
The previous requisition is closed, since the new
export requisition covers all purchasing needs.
Requisitions don't have a reference to a warehouse in
Openbravo, so we lose the information on where the
material is required. The connector will only work well
when there is only a single purchasing warehaouse.
No purchase orders are created to give the buyers the
opportunity to review them, group them,

In Openbravo only a Order has a field ScheduledDeliveryDate, not the OrderLines.
In frePPLe a single orderline can have multiple deliveries, ie partial shipments.
As a result of these mismatches we are only updating the description field of the sales order line.
Depending on the customer's needs you may want to update a different field...
